summary: I know it may sound a little insane to some of you, but I really believe that Eve has “daddy issues”. I also know that to some...
body:
I know it may sound a little insane to some of you, but I really believe that Eve has “daddy issues”. I also know that to some of you, Eve/Niko’s relationship is just about a man who loves his wife so much that all what he’s trying to do is protect her, even from herself. But, as I said in another post, all this protection is a little controlling and fatherly, and now I’m gonna show why I think that.

To be very honest, we don’t know anything about Eve, but I found it in her description from BBC’s site. Here’s the thing that struck me more. She met Niko in the hardest moment of her life, right after her dad died. She met him, when she was going to her father’s memorial, when she was vulnerable, alone, without perspective of life, she met Niko. When she was missing her father, the only person she had, she met the man who is currently her husband.

Also, as you can see, in her description, she was always trying to impress her father with her career but, when he died - I have no idea how old she was when this happened - she kind of lost all her motivation. She didn’t have any purpose on her life anymore. Not until Niko. If you look their scenes, she’s is ALWAYS looking for his approval. She’s always asking why and if he’s annoyed for doing the smallest of things. She hides things from Niko that may disappoint him.

Besides that, as I’ve said, all this sense of protection is extremely paternal. He acts like Eve is still a child who has no idea what the world is like. I know Eve’s actions are really insane, but, she’s an adult. Maybe she doesn’t know why she’s doing what she’s doing, but she knows what she’s doing. It’s not necessary for someone to remind her how dangerous her job is, and in a moment of rage she shows it:

At this point of her life, Eve may be tired of Niko’s behavior, but she’s still with him because she needs that feeling of security her father provided. Because she need someone to fill the empty that her father left. She tries to impress him with normality, because it is what he expects from her. She tries to answer all his expectations, exactly like she did with her father.

PS:. all these gifs is from @mijuoh who actually helped me with the whole post, so, thank you so much <3
